9:
Another suspicious-looking float, I
see. Your taste in destinations never
ceases to amaze me.
12: So what exactly are we doing here?
17:
I got us a job. This float wants
protection from some no-good
pirates.
27:
Now hold on, Nimbus. Surely we
cannot ignore the plea of innocent
civilians.
32: Heh, spoken like a true Champion.
36:
Our employers have done all they
can to corner the enemy. All that's
left is to work with their forces to
fight them off.
46:
Ever heard the saying "knowledge is
power"? We need information on our
enemy, so I'm going to get it.
55:
...Anyone else get the feeling she's
gonna leave us with all the dirty
work?
59:
Well, if it's for the sake of helping
others, it's fine, no?
63: *sigh* This is why you always get tric—
68:
You the mercs we hired? DAMN, that
tiger fella looks hella strong!
70:
Yeah, with you guys on our side,
those punks don't stand a chance!
75:
Yeah, right! These are pirates! The
hell is that woman thinking?!
79:
See? I told you they'd be here. I'll
leave the fighting to you.
85: The hell... Don't tell me you—
98:
Phew... That takes care of that. Now
then, ready to go?
105:
We're not goin' anywhere until you
explain yourself! We coulda been—
109:
We had to fight fire with fire. Kill two
birds with one stone... What other
phrases are there...
111:
Simply put, I got a job asking me to
clean up two particularly large piles
of trash.
114:
And by the looks of it, I did a pretty
good job.
119:
Then why did they call us
mercenaries?
122:
I had to make them think they had
the advantage. Otherwise they
wouldn't have shown up.
124:
Both groups are full of nasty fighters.
The kind you wish were locked up for
a long, long time.
126:
Does that mean... you planned this
whole damn thing?!
128:
Who do you think yer messin' with,
you—
131: Looks like I missed a spot.
135:
What do you think, Champion? I
make a pretty good protector of the
innocent, don't I?
139:
Your ways are far too devious for
such a title...
143:
But where's the fun in being a
goody-two-shoes?
146:
In any case, the navy will be here
any minute. We should get out of
here before then.
